	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Mid day posts from Gordon Wrinn</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=149451" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048480.html">Abashi, please take a moment to read this, and give me your comments!</a><P>

What I would like to see is woven armor given the leather graphic.<P> 

Bumping again,<BR>
Not asking for much here, give us a response, yes, no, we will look in to it. Something.<BR>
Please give an answer<BR>
bumping again, not stopping until I hear something<P>

<B>There are a lot of posts on the board here that people "bump" quite often in hopes of getting some sort of response. Though persistence is commendable, sometimes the content of the post where the response is being demanded isn't really something that I like to respond to.<P>

Posts from people who want an armor item with a specific look are not infrequent here on the boards. We treat it as a wishlist item and keep it in mind when creating new items. It's not the sort of thing that I want to give the impression that we are "promising" the item, nor do I want to rule it out as a possibility.<P> 

The best suggestion I can offer for things such as this are to make your opinion and desires known, but please don't demand a response, and pleasee don't feel like you are being ignored if you don't get one.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048807.html">Locked door exploits</a><P>

Fear. Not always possible due to pathing, but in some cases, you can cast fear on a mob, and he will run into door and open it.<P>

What is the position of GMs on it? Is it allowed? Or is it a bannable offense?<P>

<B>It's not considered illegal at present, but more of a design consequence. In any case, I don't think that it is as reliable as having a rogue there to open the door for you.<P>

We've been considering a few different options to eliminate this issue. One would be for all NPCs to walk through doors without opening them, like it was in beta. This looks bad though. We've got a couple other ideas that we are thinking about as well.<P>

Does anyone feel that this is an issue that needs attention? In other words, do you feel that these are reliable enough options as to decrease the importance of rogues?<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048893.html">Verant, fix the Howling Harpoon!</a><P>

The Howling Harpoon has been broken ever since discovered. I think its about time to get it fixed. As of right now, Memory Blur procs on yourself, the player. It has no effect whatsoever and doesn't have a purpose this way.<P>

<B>We are aware of this problem. We're still trying to decide what spell-effect to put on it.<P>

Thanks.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048965.html">Abashi, would you please answer a quick question about current poison components?</a><P>

Unlike many of my brethren, I continue to use my poison skill. I have quite a stockpile of Asp poison sacks, Putrid Biles, Ashroots and Embalming Dusts in the bank, along with appropriate vials for each. With the new changes due to be implemented at the end of this month, will those supplies be negated? Are we looking at completely new components, or will the same ones be used?<P>

<B>It's too soon for me to say how many of the existing components will continue to be usable with the new recipies. One of the guys was creating a bunch of new components yesterday and is putting the new recipies together. Assuming that we follow the same logic as before with the Alchemy revamp, existing poisons should continue to be makeable, but new ones will probably require new components. I really need to sit down with the designer before I'll be able to comment intelligently though, which I probably won't do until the new system has been approved.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048974.html">Serious breach of policy on Rallos Zek</a><P>

I am reposting this issue from the ralloszek.net OOC forum. It involves a former abusive player on Rallos Zek who has close personal ties with Brad McQuaid and has since become a Lead-GM on Rallos Zek. This issue transcends the coin loot issue and leads credence to a true conspiracy.<P>

<B>First, lets get off this idea that any time something happens that is questionable that the people involved must have "close personal ties with Brad McQuaid". No one working here has close enough personal ties with anyone that they would put the integrity of the game at risk.<P> 

That said, this is a coincidence. With several million characters in existence, it was only a matter of time before a GM begining work here chose a name that had some history on a particular server. When things of this nature happens, we investigate the issue to insure that integrity is maintained. We're having the GM choose a new name since this one evidently caused quite a stir on Rallos.<P> 

Furthermore I should mention that that particular GM isn't the GM for Rallos. He was just in the process of creating his GM name across all of the servers when he was spied in the /who list.</B><P> 

On my origional post on this topic, a Verant emploee with the screen name Verant_Thom agreed to look into this.<BR>
Does anyone know who this is in the Verant Hierarchy?<P>

<B>He's the Customer Service Manager for EverQuest. Jeff Butler was promoted to the position of Producer of EQLive back in March.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048977.html">Why wasn't the weight on the Tranquil Staff reduced??</a><P>

I know it is a powerful weapon, but monks are supposed to be powerful. This weapon may outclass many available to other classes but monks are in general able to wield more powerful weapons. We are given the ability to do more melee damage in exchange for our weight penalty, inability to wear many types of armor, inability to use slashing and piercing weapons, etc. <P>

So why is it this staff is unchanged in the patch? Is it a balance issue to make us sacrafice AC in order to do damage? No other class has this problem; a 10 lb weapon is very heavy, but doable for them. For monks, it would mean we have to have only 4 lbs worth of other equipment, which is simply not feasible. Can you please explain the decision on this?<P>

<B>Some of the weapon weights are intentional. I will check to insure that they got all of the ones that were mistaken, but the tranquil staff is one of those that is meant to be very heavy (monk-wise anyway). It's an incredibly powerful weapon and needed a pretty substantial drawback.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048978.html">Stealth Enhancements</a><P>

<B>This morning I was handed a list of spell changes that didn't make it into the patch message. I'll put up an addendum later today, but here's the list for review:<P>

* Banshee Aura has had its duration increased.
<BR>* Scale of Wolf and Spirit of Scale will no longer be canceled by being the target of a melee attack. Ranged attacks and spells will still cancel the spell.
<BR>* Shaman can now cast Charm Animal
<BR>* Some enchanter and shaman spells have had their casting times/mana costs altered.
<BR>* Augment, Glamour of Kintaz, Rapture, and Clarity II have had their mana cost lowered.
<BR>* Root spells that cause damage (Druid roots, Hungry Earth) now work properly.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

Hmmm... correct me if I amwrong (and I amSURE you will) but isn't this the FOURTH time that root with damage has been "fixed"? <P>

<B>Actually I believe it's the third. But we're serious this time. Sorry for the problem getting these resolved.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048984.html">I heard of kick with integral stun but ?</a><P>

I play a Champion lvl 51, and I heard, a long time ago, that we got kick with integral stuns.
I didnt notice any at lvl 1 to 50, so I though it was at lvl 51+, but I didnt notice any stun effect on my kicks. so the question is: I am dumb, is it higher level or I heard something wrong ?<P>

<B>Yes, kicks with an integral chance to stun are indeed an ability gained by warriors post-50. I have not though commented on what level the ability is gained.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<A href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/048993.html">Jolt - Does Verant listen AT ALL?!</a><P>

I can't believe the thick-skulled nature of these guys!
Level 55. Casting time 3.5 seconds. This is absolutely ludicrous. Let me say it now: this spell is absolutely worthless.<P>

<B>You haven't even tried the spell yet. Chances are that if you back off as soon as the critter turns on to you, it won't follow you assuming that you've got a group beating on it. <P>

It's a spell that you didn't have access to before. At least give it a shot before coming here complaining about it being useless.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049012.html">PvP?! What the heck?</a><P>

Is it true that the class/race balancing has been designed around PvP concerns?! What the heck is that? I would bet that more than 3/4 of the players are not Player Killers... Why not design our characters to make them more fun trying to kill NPC's!!! HEhe just IMHO<P>

<B>Player classes are not balanced in terms of PvP offensive power. What I mean by this is that we didn't throw each class in a pit and hold one on one battles in some effort to create equality. Classes are balanced primarily for Player versus Environment (PvE).<P>
 
We've had to make a few changes to the way things work in PvP in order to deal some balance issues that pop up. For example, in PvP, spells do 2/3rds damage versus another player. This is because the spells are designed to be effective versus NPCs, and are much too strong versus players who often have far less hitpoints than an equalently leveled NPC. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049023.html">New Patch issues</a><P>

Ok, I have three small issues with the new patch. First, didn't you say the Druid root series would be fixed? We've been waiting FOREVER.<P>

<B>Yes, it's in today. I'll post it in the patch message addendum.</B><P>

Secondly you said, "Illusions are defined as any spell that makes a character look different than they actually are. This includes all racial illusions, as well as other illusions such as Treeform, Wolfform, and the Call of Bones series." How many times have you told us that wolfform/treeform ARE NOT illusions?<P> 

<B>From an RP standpoint, they are not illusions. From a programming standpoint, they are handled the same way.</B><P> 

And lastly, you said, "there are many cases where a solitary and stationary outdoor creature has a "fast spawn", yielding the reward of fast experience-gain without the commensurate risk." How do you figure? Any time you attack a creature there is risk, not to mention a single spawn will not give you the XP/loot that a good dungeon group will.<P> 

<B>And example of a "fast spawn" is something that spawns much faster than a critter in a dungeon at a similar level would. For example, a level 40 critter spawning every 6 minutes would be a "fast spawn". Now if this spawn is stationary and solitary, the risk is reduced tremendously. That's what I was trying to point out.</B><P>

Quit trying to NERF everything<P> 

<B>We've still made far more enhancements to the game that people would consider generally positive in nature than we have made ones that they'd consider negative. Regardless of how people view the change, we feel that they are in the best interest of the game overall.<P>

For example, in regards to those fast spawns, people will often sit there and camp them for hour after hour, doing an admitedly boring and repetitive task because they view it to be "faster". In the mean time, they are bored to death. Our goal in these cases is to make doing more exciting things, such as fighting in a dungeon, "faster". This way people are having fun while leveling up instead of being bored from camping one creature for hours. That's the goal anyway.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/049050.html">Hey Gordon...</a><P>

Quick two questions: First off... why does a combine dagger cost less than a fine steel? A combine dagger in North Karana costs around 36pp, with a fine steel costing 48pp.... any comments on that?<P>

<B>Fine steel weapons sell at a large premium on vendors because we prefer that players trade amongst themselves for the weapons. It's basically to spur the economy on. We really wouldn't expect that anyone would actually pay for a fine steel weapon from a vendor considering the price.</B><P>

Second, is there any place to submit ideas for new quests? I've got a few ideas on them....<P>

<B>/feedback in game is a good idea at the moment. Soon we'll be publicizing some email addresses for quest ideas as well as one to help players coordinate events that require GM assistance.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
